cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.CV, cs.AR, cs.ET 

The paper introduces a new algorithm for image and video compression using a multiplierless pruned approximate 8-point discrete cosine transform (DCT). This suggests that the paper could belong to the following sub-categories: 

- cs.MM (Multimedia): This sub-category deals with multimedia systems, including image and video processing. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): Information theory is concerned with the quantification, storage, and communication of information. The proposed algorithm could fall under this category as it involves compression and encoding of information. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Computer vision deals with the analysis and interpretation of images and videos. The proposed algorithm could be relevant to this sub-category as it involves image and video compression. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper also discusses the digital implementation of the algorithm in 45 nm CMOS technology, which could fall under this sub-category. 
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems): Embedded systems involve the integration of hardware and software to perform specific functions. The digital implementation of the algorithm could also be relevant to this sub-category.
